📘 Your CompTIA A+ – Interview Q&A Revision Sheet

Here are all questions + perfect answers we covered so far 👇

1. What is RAM?

👉 “RAM (Random Access Memory) is temporary memory that stores data of currently running programs so the CPU can access it quickly. It helps in improving system speed and multitasking.”

2. Which is faster: HDD or SSD?

👉 “SSD is faster than HDD because it uses flash memory with no moving parts, while HDD uses spinning disks, which makes it slower.”

3. What is CPU?

👉 “CPU (Central Processing Unit) is the brain of the computer that processes instructions and performs calculations and logical operations.”

4. What is a core in CPU?

👉 “A core is a processing unit inside the CPU. More cores allow the system to handle multiple tasks simultaneously.”

5. Can DDR4 fit in DDR3 slot?

👉 “No, DDR4 cannot fit into a DDR3 slot because they have different physical designs and are not compatible.”

6. User says system is slow — what will you check?

👉
“I will check RAM usage, CPU usage, disk performance, and background applications. If the system is using HDD, I may suggest upgrading to SSD for better performance.”

7. System is not turning ON — what will you check?

👉
“I will check the power cable, power supply (SMPS), and ensure all internal connections are properly connected. If needed, I will test with another power cable or SMPS.”

8. What is SMPS?

👉
“SMPS is a power supply unit that converts AC to DC and distributes power to all computer components.”

9. System is ON but no display — what will you check?

👉
“I will check the display cable and monitor, then reseat or check the RAM, and verify the display port or GPU.”

10. What is motherboard?

👉
“Motherboard is the main circuit board of a computer that connects and allows communication between all components like CPU, RAM, and storage.”

11. Name any 3 components connected to motherboard

👉 CPU, RAM, Storage (HDD/SSD)

12. What is HDMI?

👉
“HDMI is used to transmit both audio and video from computer to display.”

13. What is VGA?

👉
“VGA is an older video port that supports only video signals.”

14. What is USB?

👉
“USB (Universal Serial Bus) is used to connect peripheral devices like keyboard, mouse, and storage devices.”

15. What is LAN port?

👉
“LAN port is used to connect a system to a network using an Ethernet cable.”

16. USB not working — what will you do?

👉
“I will check the USB port, test the device on another system, try a different port, restart the system, and check USB drivers.”

17. What is peripheral device?

👉
“Peripheral devices are external hardware connected to a computer, such as keyboard, mouse, and printer.”

18. USB full form?

👉 “Universal Serial Bus”

19. Difference between input and output device?

👉
“Input devices are used to give instructions to the computer, such as keyboard and mouse. Output devices are used to display results, such as monitor and printer.”

